# intersection.rules
# Austerity DSL — Traffic intersection controller — Junction 14

AUSTERITY 0.1
#
# This file defines the decision logic for a four-way autonomous
# traffic intersection. It is the complete rule set for the MVP demo.
#
# Rules are evaluated in the order they are declared.
# If two rules write to the same key in the same step,
# the rule declared LAST takes precedence.
#
# The phase cycle under normal conditions is:
#
#   NORTH_SOUTH_GREEN
#         |
#   NORTH_SOUTH_YELLOW
#         |
#   ALL_RED  (clearance = true)   <-- vehicles clear the intersection
#         |
#   EAST_WEST_GREEN
#         |
#   EAST_WEST_YELLOW
#         |
#   ALL_RED  (clearance = true)   <-- vehicles clear the intersection
#         |
#   NORTH_SOUTH_GREEN  (and so on)
#
# ALL_RED has two distinct meanings:
#
#   clearance = true  — normal interval between phase transitions.
#                       All directions hold red briefly so vehicles
#                       already in the intersection can clear safely.
#                       Trucks, long vehicles and late crossers are
#                       the primary beneficiaries of this interval.
#
#   emergency = true  — an emergency vehicle is approaching.
#                       All directions hold red until emergency clears.
#
# These two conditions are mutually exclusive by design.
# The clearance and emergency flags in state make the distinction
# unambiguous for both the engine and the human reading the log.
#
# Rules: 11 total
#   Section 1 — Normal phase rotation   (6 rules)
#   Section 2 — Queue pressure          (3 rules)
#   Section 3 — Emergency response      (2 rules)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------


# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# SECTION 1 — Normal phase rotation
#
# These six rules advance the lights through the standard cycle.
# Yellow phases transition to an all-red clearance interval before
# the opposing direction receives a green signal.
#
# The clearance flag is set to true when entering a normal ALL_RED
# interval, and back to false when leaving it. This allows the
# emergency rules in Section 3 to remain unambiguous.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

RULE north_south_green_to_yellow
WHEN phase = "NORTH_SOUTH_GREEN" AND cycle_timer = 0
THEN
    phase       = "NORTH_SOUTH_YELLOW"
    cycle_timer = 5
END

RULE north_south_yellow_to_clearance
WHEN phase = "NORTH_SOUTH_YELLOW" AND cycle_timer = 0
THEN
    phase       = "ALL_RED"
    clearance   = true
    cycle_timer = 3
END

RULE clearance_to_east_west_green
WHEN phase = "ALL_RED" AND clearance = true AND cycle_timer = 0
THEN
    phase       = "EAST_WEST_GREEN"
    clearance   = false
    cycle_timer = cycle_time
END

RULE east_west_green_to_yellow
WHEN phase = "EAST_WEST_GREEN" AND cycle_timer = 0
THEN
    phase       = "EAST_WEST_YELLOW"
    cycle_timer = 5
END

RULE east_west_yellow_to_clearance
WHEN phase = "EAST_WEST_YELLOW" AND cycle_timer = 0
THEN
    phase       = "ALL_RED"
    clearance   = true
    cycle_timer = 3
END

RULE clearance_to_north_south_green
WHEN phase = "ALL_RED" AND clearance = true AND cycle_timer = 0
THEN
    phase       = "NORTH_SOUTH_GREEN"
    clearance   = false
    cycle_timer = cycle_time
END


# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# SECTION 2 — Queue pressure adjustments
#
# These rules extend or shorten the active green phase depending
# on how much traffic is waiting. They only fire during green
# phases — yellow and clearance phases are never extended.
#
# Extension adds steps directly to cycle_timer when a queue
# is heavy. It does not change cycle_time, which remains the
# default reset value for the next full phase.
#
# Reduction fires when all queues are light, trimming the
# remaining timer so the cycle moves on sooner. The engine
# clamps cycle_timer at zero — it will never go negative
# regardless of how aggressively this rule fires.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

RULE extend_north_south_on_heavy_load
WHEN phase = "NORTH_SOUTH_GREEN" AND north_queue > 10
THEN
    cycle_timer = cycle_timer + 10
END

RULE extend_east_west_on_heavy_load
WHEN phase = "EAST_WEST_GREEN" AND east_queue > 10
THEN
    cycle_timer = cycle_timer + 10
END

RULE reduce_cycle_on_low_traffic
WHEN north_queue < 3 AND south_queue < 3 AND east_queue < 3 AND west_queue < 3
THEN
    cycle_timer = cycle_timer - 5
END


# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# SECTION 3 — Emergency response
#
# These two rules handle the full emergency lifecycle.
#
# emergency_override fires every step that emergency = true.
# It forces ALL_RED, zeroes the timer, and ensures clearance
# remains false — distinguishing this state from a normal
# clearance interval. No rotation rule can fire while this
# rule is active, because they all test for specific phases
# or for clearance = true.
#
# emergency_recovery fires on the first step after emergency
# clears. It returns the intersection to NORTH_SOUTH_GREEN
# and resets the timer to a full cycle, resuming normal
# operation cleanly from a known state.
#
# Declaration order note: emergency_override is declared before
# emergency_recovery. Because last-declared wins on key conflicts,
# recovery takes precedence if both conditions were simultaneously
# true — which cannot happen by definition, but the ordering is
# documented here for clarity and future maintainability.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

RULE emergency_override
WHEN emergency = true
THEN
    phase       = "ALL_RED"
    clearance   = false
    cycle_timer = 0
END

RULE emergency_recovery
WHEN emergency = false AND phase = "ALL_RED" AND clearance = false
THEN
    phase       = "NORTH_SOUTH_GREEN"
    cycle_timer = cycle_time
END
